[I] tiny but flexible init system and process supervisor

[T] Nitro is a tiny process supervisor that also can be used as pid 1 on Linux.

[U] https://git.vuxu.org/nitro/

[A] Leah Neukirchen <leah@vuxu.org>
[M] The T2 Project <t2@t2-project.org>

[C] extra/tool
[F] CROSS

[L] OpenSource
[V] 0.8

[D] c3b4119eef74b6326feb566a8fe28d125d5c60f16803527ee4f671b4 nitro-0.8.tar.gz https://git.vuxu.org/nitro/snapshot/

makeinstopt=
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -vf {nitro,nitroctl} $root$bindir/'
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -vf nitroctl.1 $root$mandir/man1/'
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -vf nitro.8 $root$mandir/man8/'
